 dweller\" in Greek. The specific name, musicus, is Latin and means \"musical\". Description The Saint Vincent wren has reddish-brown upperparts contrasting with whitish underparts, the wings and tailare barred with dark and tail, a pale supercilium and face with reddish-brown with darker speckling on the breast, sides and undertail. It has a buzzing call and the song is sweet and musical. Distribution and habitat The Saint Vincent wren is endemic to the island of Saint Vincent in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, here it is found from montane evergreen forests and brushy woodlands to farmland and built up areas. References", "shortSummary": "The St. Vincent wren (Troglodytes musicus) is a very small passerine bird in the wren family Troglodytidae that is found on the Caribbean i…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Troglodytes_musicus_-_David_J_Barton_-_473175108.jpeg/960px-Troglodytes_musicus_-_David_J_Barton_-_473175108.jpeg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-troglodytes", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-troglodytes-musicus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-troglodytes", "species": "taxonomy-species-troglodytes-musicus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 128.99, "y": 739.61, "z": -569.68}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-troglodytes", "name": "Troglodytes", "latinName": "Troglodytes", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Troglodytes（Troglodytes）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联18种鸟类，如Northern house wren、Cozumel wren、Kalinago wren等18种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 18, "x": -531.22, "y": 467.5, "z": 41.87}], "links": [{"key": "bird-st-vincent-wren-c3534298__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-troglodytes-musicus", "source": "bird-st-vincent-wren-c3534298", "target": "taxonomy-species-troglodytes-musicus", 